statements.sql: select count(*) as aggregate from `jobs_data` where `jobs_data`.`deleted_at` is null
select * from `jobs_data` where `jobs_data`.`deleted_at` is null order by `id` desc limit 25 offset 0

select `certificates`.*, `job_certificates`.`job_id` as `pivot_job_id`, `job_certificates`.`certificate_id` as `pivot_certificate_id` from `certificates` inner join `job_certificates` on `certificates`.`id` = `job_certificates`.`certificate_id` where `job_certificates`.`job_id` in (10, 26, 45, 46, 47, 48, 50, 54, 55, 58) and `certificates`.`deleted_at` is null

select `abilities`.*, `job_abilities`.`job_id` as `pivot_job_id`, `job_abilities`.`ability_id` as `pivot_ability_id` from `abilities` inner join `job_abilities` on `abilities`.`id` = `job_abilities`.`ability_id` where `job_abilities`.`job_id` in (10, 26, 45, 46, 47, 48, 50, 54, 55, 58) and `abilities`.`deleted_at` is null

select `knowledge`.*, `job_knowledge`.`job_id` as `pivot_job_id`, `job_knowledge`.`knowledge_id` as `pivot_knowledge_id` from `knowledge` inner join `job_knowledge` on `knowledge`.`id` = `job_knowledge`.`knowledge_id` where `job_knowledge`.`job_id` in (10, 26, 45, 46, 47, 48, 50, 54, 55, 58) and `knowledge`.`deleted_at` is null

select `educations`.*, `job_educations`.`job_id` as `pivot_job_id`, `job_educations`.`education_id` as `pivot_education_id` from `educations` inner join `job_educations` on `educations`.`id` = `job_educations`.`education_id` where `job_educations`.`job_id` in (10, 26, 45, 46, 47, 48, 50, 54, 55, 58)

select `work_contexts`.*, `job_work_contexts`.`job_id` as `pivot_job_id`, `job_work_contexts`.`work_id` as `pivot_work_id` from `work_contexts` inner join `job_work_contexts` on `work_contexts`.`id` = `job_work_contexts`.`work_id` where `job_work_contexts`.`job_id` in (10, 26, 45, 46, 47, 48, 50, 54, 55, 58) and `work_contexts`.`deleted_at` is null
